summary: This is an email chain from December 6, 2019, forwarding a November 10, 2019 email regarding the results of a subpoena for Ghislaine Maxwell's cell phone records from T-Mobile. The email includes attachments of call detail records and subscriber information, and is sent between law enforcement personnel on the NYPD/FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Her cell phone number is the subject of the subpoena and records request from T-Mobile as part of case number 561616.

events.title: T-Mobile sends records for Maxwell's number
events.description: T-Mobile sends an email with the subject 'Tasks for Case Number: 561616' containing records for Ghislaine Maxwell's cell phone number in response to a subpoena.

events.title: FBI forwards T-Mobile records
events.description: An FBI agent forwards the T-Mobile records email to other law enforcement personnel on the NYPD/FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force.

events.title: Maxwell cell phone subpoena results forwarded
events.description: The email chain regarding the subpoena results for Maxwell's cell phone is forwarded again, with the subject 'Maxwell cell phone subpoena results'.

keyFacts: A subpoena was issued for Ghislaine Maxwell's cell phone records from T-Mobile as part of case number 561616.
The records were provided by T-Mobile on November 9, 2019, and forwarded within the NYPD/FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force.
The email includes multiple attachments such as call detail records (CDR), a certification, and interpretation guides for the data.
The communication demonstrates active law enforcement investigation into Maxwell in late 2019.
The document is part of the evidence set (Data Set 9) in the Epstein case files.
